title: Infant Mortality Rate for Countries with Fragile and Conflict Affected Situations
notes:
Infant mortality rate is the number of infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 live births in a given year.

Nations that are included in this data series are listed at http://www.worldbank.org/en/topic/fragilityconflictviolence/overview

Source Indicator: SP.DYN.IMRT.IN
